40static int
41gk104_fifo_gpfifo_kick(struct gk104_fifo_chan *chan)
42{
43 struct gk104_fifo *fifo = chan->fifo;
44 struct nvkm_subdev *subdev = &fifo->base.engine.subdev;
45 struct nvkm_device *device = subdev->device;
46 struct nvkm_client *client = chan->base.object.client;
47 int ret = 0;
48
49 mutex_lock(&subdev->mutex);
50 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x002634, chan->base.chid);
51 if (nvkm_msec(device, 2000,
52 if (!(nvkm_rd32(device, 0x002634) & 0x00100000))
53 break;
54 ) < 0) {
55 nvkm_error(subdev, "channel %d [%s] kick timeout\n",
56 chan->base.chid, client->name);
57 ret = -ETIMEDOUT;
58 }
59 mutex_unlock(&subdev->mutex);
60 return ret;
61}
62
63static u32
64gk104_fifo_gpfifo_engine_addr(struct nvkm_engine *engine)
65{
66 switch (engine->subdev.index) {
67 case NVKM_ENGINE_SW :
68 case NVKM_ENGINE_CE0 :
69 case NVKM_ENGINE_CE1 :
70 case NVKM_ENGINE_CE2 : return 0x0000;
71 case NVKM_ENGINE_GR : return 0x0210;
72 case NVKM_ENGINE_MSPDEC: return 0x0250;
73 case NVKM_ENGINE_MSPPP : return 0x0260;
74 case NVKM_ENGINE_MSVLD : return 0x0270;
75 default:
76 WARN_ON(1);
77 return 0;
78 }
79}
80
81static int
82gk104_fifo_gpfifo_engine_fini(struct nvkm_fifo_chan *base,
83 struct nvkm_engine *engine, bool suspend)
84{
85 const u32 offset = gk104_fifo_gpfifo_engine_addr(engine);
86 struct gk104_fifo_chan *chan = gk104_fifo_chan(base);
87 struct nvkm_gpuobj *inst = chan->base.inst;
88 int ret;
89
90 ret = gk104_fifo_gpfifo_kick(chan);
91 if (ret && suspend)
92 return ret;
93
94 if (offset) {
95 nvkm_kmap(inst);
96 nvkm_wo32(inst, offset + 0x00, 0x00000000);
97 nvkm_wo32(inst, offset + 0x04, 0x00000000);
98 nvkm_done(inst);
99 }
100
101 return ret;
102}
103
104static int
105gk104_fifo_gpfifo_engine_init(struct nvkm_fifo_chan *base,
106 struct nvkm_engine *engine)
107{
108 const u32 offset = gk104_fifo_gpfifo_engine_addr(engine);
109 struct gk104_fifo_chan *chan = gk104_fifo_chan(base);
110 struct nvkm_gpuobj *inst = chan->base.inst;
111
112 if (offset) {
113 u64 addr = chan->engn[engine->subdev.index].vma.offset;
114 nvkm_kmap(inst);
115 nvkm_wo32(inst, offset + 0x00, lower_32_bits(addr) | 4);
116 nvkm_wo32(inst, offset + 0x04, upper_32_bits(addr));
117 nvkm_done(inst);
118 }
119
120 return 0;
121}
122
123static void
124gk104_fifo_gpfifo_engine_dtor(struct nvkm_fifo_chan *base,
125 struct nvkm_engine *engine)
126{
127 struct gk104_fifo_chan *chan = gk104_fifo_chan(base);
128 nvkm_gpuobj_unmap(&chan->engn[engine->subdev.index].vma);
129 nvkm_gpuobj_del(&chan->engn[engine->subdev.index].inst);
130}
131
132static int
133gk104_fifo_gpfifo_engine_ctor(struct nvkm_fifo_chan *base,
134 struct nvkm_engine *engine,
135 struct nvkm_object *object)
136{
137 struct gk104_fifo_chan *chan = gk104_fifo_chan(base);
138 int engn = engine->subdev.index;
139 int ret;
140
141 if (!gk104_fifo_gpfifo_engine_addr(engine))
142 return 0;
143
144 ret = nvkm_object_bind(object, NULL, 0, &chan->engn[engn].inst);
145 if (ret)
146 return ret;
147
148 return nvkm_gpuobj_map(chan->engn[engn].inst, chan->vm,
149 NV_MEM_ACCESS_RW, &chan->engn[engn].vma);
150}
151
152static void
153gk104_fifo_gpfifo_fini(struct nvkm_fifo_chan *base)
154{
155 struct gk104_fifo_chan *chan = gk104_fifo_chan(base);
156 struct gk104_fifo *fifo = chan->fifo;
157 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->base.engine.subdev.device;
158 u32 coff = chan->base.chid * 8;
159
160 if (!list_empty(&chan->head)) {
161 list_del_init(&chan->head);
162 nvkm_mask(device, 0x800004 + coff, 0x00000800, 0x00000800);
163 gk104_fifo_runlist_update(fifo, chan->engine);
164 }
165
166 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x800000 + coff, 0x00000000);
167}
168
169static void
170gk104_fifo_gpfifo_init(struct nvkm_fifo_chan *base)
171{
172 struct gk104_fifo_chan *chan = gk104_fifo_chan(base);
173 struct gk104_fifo *fifo = chan->fifo;
174 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->base.engine.subdev.device;
175 u32 addr = chan->base.inst->addr >> 12;
176 u32 coff = chan->base.chid * 8;
177
178 nvkm_mask(device, 0x800004 + coff, 0x000f0000, chan->engine << 16);
179 nvkm_wr32(device, 0x800000 + coff, 0x80000000 | addr);
180
181 if (list_empty(&chan->head) && !chan->killed) {
182 list_add_tail(&chan->head, &fifo->engine[chan->engine].chan);
183 nvkm_mask(device, 0x800004 + coff, 0x00000400, 0x00000400);
184 gk104_fifo_runlist_update(fifo, chan->engine);
185 nvkm_mask(device, 0x800004 + coff, 0x00000400, 0x00000400);
186 }
187}
188
189static void *
190gk104_fifo_gpfifo_dtor(struct nvkm_fifo_chan *base)
191{
192 struct gk104_fifo_chan *chan = gk104_fifo_chan(base);
193 nvkm_vm_ref(NULL, &chan->vm, chan->pgd);
194 nvkm_gpuobj_del(&chan->pgd);
195 return chan;
196}
197
198static const struct nvkm_fifo_chan_func
199gk104_fifo_gpfifo_func = {
200 .dtor = gk104_fifo_gpfifo_dtor,
201 .init = gk104_fifo_gpfifo_init,
202 .fini = gk104_fifo_gpfifo_fini,
203 .ntfy = g84_fifo_chan_ntfy,
204 .engine_ctor = gk104_fifo_gpfifo_engine_ctor,
205 .engine_dtor = gk104_fifo_gpfifo_engine_dtor,
206 .engine_init = gk104_fifo_gpfifo_engine_init,
207 .engine_fini = gk104_fifo_gpfifo_engine_fini,
208};
209
210int
211gk104_fifo_gpfifo_new(struct nvkm_fifo *base, const struct nvkm_oclass *oclass,
212 void *data, u32 size, struct nvkm_object **pobject)
213{
214 union {
215 struct kepler_channel_gpfifo_a_v0 v0;
216 } *args = data;
217 struct gk104_fifo *fifo = gk104_fifo(base);
218 struct nvkm_device *device = fifo->base.engine.subdev.device;
219 struct nvkm_object *parent = oclass->parent;
220 struct gk104_fifo_chan *chan;
221 u64 usermem, ioffset, ilength;
222 u32 engines;
223 int ret, i;
224
225 nvif_ioctl(parent, "create channel gpfifo size %d\n", size);
226 if (nvif_unpack(args->v0, 0, 0, false)) {
227 nvif_ioctl(parent, "create channel gpfifo vers %d vm %"PRIx64" "
228 "ioffset %016"PRIx64" ilength %08x engine %08x\n",
229 args->v0.version, args->v0.vm, args->v0.ioffset,
230 args->v0.ilength, args->v0.engine);
231 } else
232 return ret;
233
234 /* determine which downstream engines are present */
235 for (i = 0, engines = 0; i < ARRAY_SIZE(fifo->engine); i++) {
236 u64 subdevs = gk104_fifo_engine_subdev(i);
237 if (!nvkm_device_engine(device, __ffs64(subdevs)))
238 continue;
239 engines |= (1 << i);
240 }
241
242 /* if this is an engine mask query, we're done */
243 if (!args->v0.engine) {
244 args->v0.engine = engines;
245 return nvkm_object_new(oclass, NULL, 0, pobject);
246 }
247
248 /* check that we support a requested engine - note that the user
249 * argument is a mask in order to allow the user to request (for
250 * example) *any* copy engine, but doesn't matter which.
251 */
252 args->v0.engine &= engines;
253 if (!args->v0.engine) {
254 nvif_ioctl(parent, "no supported engine\n");
255 return -ENODEV;
256 }
257
258 /* allocate the channel */
259 if (!(chan = kzalloc(sizeof(*chan), GFP_KERNEL)))
260 return -ENOMEM;
261 *pobject = &chan->base.object;
262 chan->fifo = fifo;
263 chan->engine = __ffs(args->v0.engine);
264 INIT_LIST_HEAD(&chan->head);
265
266 ret = nvkm_fifo_chan_ctor(&gk104_fifo_gpfifo_func, &fifo->base,
267 0x1000, 0x1000, true, args->v0.vm, 0,
268 gk104_fifo_engine_subdev(chan->engine),
269 1, fifo->user.bar.offset, 0x200,
270 oclass, &chan->base);
271 if (ret)
272 return ret;
273
274 args->v0.chid = chan->base.chid;
275
276 /* page directory */
277 ret = nvkm_gpuobj_new(device, 0x10000, 0x1000, false, NULL, &chan->pgd);
278 if (ret)
279 return ret;
280
281 nvkm_kmap(chan->base.inst);
282 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x0200, lower_32_bits(chan->pgd->addr));
283 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x0204, upper_32_bits(chan->pgd->addr));
284 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x0208, 0xffffffff);
285 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x020c, 0x000000ff);
286 nvkm_done(chan->base.inst);
287
288 ret = nvkm_vm_ref(chan->base.vm, &chan->vm, chan->pgd);
289 if (ret)
290 return ret;
291
292 /* clear channel control registers */
293 usermem = chan->base.chid * 0x200;
294 ioffset = args->v0.ioffset;
295 ilength = order_base_2(args->v0.ilength / 8);
296
297 nvkm_kmap(fifo->user.mem);
298 for (i = 0; i < 0x200; i += 4)
299 nvkm_wo32(fifo->user.mem, usermem + i, 0x00000000);
300 nvkm_done(fifo->user.mem);
301 usermem = nvkm_memory_addr(fifo->user.mem) + usermem;
302
303 /* RAMFC */
304 nvkm_kmap(chan->base.inst);
305 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x08, lower_32_bits(usermem));
306 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x0c, upper_32_bits(usermem));
307 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x10, 0x0000face);
308 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x30, 0xfffff902);
309 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x48, lower_32_bits(ioffset));
310 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x4c, upper_32_bits(ioffset) |
311 (ilength << 16));
312 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x84, 0x20400000);
313 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x94, 0x30000001);
314 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0x9c, 0x00000100);
315 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0xac, 0x0000001f);
316 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0xe8, chan->base.chid);
317 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0xb8, 0xf8000000);
318 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0xf8, 0x10003080); /* 0x002310 */
319 nvkm_wo32(chan->base.inst, 0xfc, 0x10000010); /* 0x002350 */
320 nvkm_done(chan->base.inst);
321 return 0;
322}
323
324const struct nvkm_fifo_chan_oclass
325gk104_fifo_gpfifo_oclass = {
326 .base.oclass = KEPLER_CHANNEL_GPFIFO_A,
327 .base.minver = 0,
328 .base.maxver = 0,
329 .ctor = gk104_fifo_gpfifo_new,
330};
